<br>
Is Pacifica a Secessionist State? <br>
<br>
No. Pacifica is not attempting to &quot;secede&quot; from any existing territorial state in order to create a new territorial state. <br>
<br>
Is Pacifica a &quot;micronation&quot;? <br>
<br>
No. &quot;Micronations&quot; are state-like entities that exist only on the internet. They do not have a verifiable existence in the real world or any sustainable claim to legitimacy. <br>
<br>
Pacifica is a club or a political simulation? <br>
<br>
No. The operations of Pacifica are real, and are directed towards the goal of eventual formal recognition by the wider community of nations. <br>
<br>
Are you a commercial enterprise? <br>
<br>
No. Pacifica does not exist to make money. All official and administrative roles within the Empire are undertaken on a voluntary basis, and all funds generated via the sale of official merchandise, passports, postage stamps, banknotes either directly support the Empire's ongoing operations or are donated to international charitable, aid and cultural organisations. <br>
<br>
What is Pacifica then? <br>
<br>
The Empire of Pacifica is a legitimate, functioning, primarily non-territorial MicroState that possesses immanent, virtual global sovereignty. The purpose of Pacifica is to promote, via its very real existence, the fact that sovereignty in the modern world does not need to have any form of territorial basis. <br>
<br>
Is Pacifica a real country? <br>
<br>
Yes. Pacifica is a self-declared State possessing the fully functioning apparatus, institutions and representative symbols of an independent, sovereign entity, including a population, a Constitution, judicial system, elected legislature, flags and insignia, a monetary system and diplomatic representation, amongst others. <br>
In this respect it is important to note the following articles from the 1933 Montevideo Convention on the Rights and Duties of States, which form the traditional internationally accepted basis for the legal definition of statehood: <br>
<br>
Article 1: The state as a person of international law should possess the following qualifications: <br>
<br>
1. A permanent population; <br>
2. A defined territory; <br>
3. A government; and <br>
4. A capacity to enter into relations with the other states. <br>
<br>
Article 3: The political existence of the state is independent of recognition by the other states. Even before recognition the state has the right to defend its integrity and independence, to provide for its conservation and prosperity, and consequently to organize itself as it sees fit, to legislate upon its interests, administer its services, and to define the jurisdiction and competence of its courts. <br>
<br>
Is Pacifica a Dictatorial State? <br>
<br>
No, The Empire of Pacifica is far from that. According to the Holy Constitution of 2000, the State of Pacifica is a Constitutional Monarchy; this means that we have a Senate and a government elected by the people in free and democratically elections. The Emperor only represents the State and can intervene in some moderation. <br>
<br>
Does Pacifica possess any territory? <br>
<br>
Yes. Pacifica possesses 240 square metre enclave inside the City of Porto, Portugal. this has a permanent population, forms the sole territorial claim of the Empire, and is its official Capital. <br>
<br>
How is it possible for a country to exist with virtually no territory? <br>
<br>
Several such recognised states already exist. The Vatican City for example possesses only a few hectares of land and has a mere handful of citizens, also the Sovereign Military Order of Malta has existed as a state without territory since its expulsion from the island of Malta nearly two centuries ago. Both of the aforementioned are widely recognised by UN Member States. <br>
<br>
In light of the above, what do you mean when you say Pacifica is a primarily non-territorial state? <br>
<br>
Pacifica believes that territorial claims as the basis for statehood mean very little in the present day. <br>
It is a key contention that whilst Article 1(b) of the Montevideo Convention has hitherto generally comprised the major qualifier for the determination of legitimate statehood, the increasing mobility of global populations, and their ability to communicate and to form communities across or without reference to territorial boundaries render this definition increasingly less relevant. <br>
<br>
We therefore assert that the primary legitimacy of Pacifica should be determined by its de facto existence as represented by its community of Citizens - wherever they happen to be distributed geographically - and its operating institutions - not solely on the basis of its territorial claims. <br>
<br>
How serious are you? <br>
<br>
Quite serious. Pacifica's Declaration of Independence was unilateral and remains unrecognised, however that does not alter the fact of the Empire's existence. At 240 square metres we qualify as one of the world's smallest territorial State. That of course brings into play certain practical realities, and we choose to deal with these in a pragmatic manner. We also recognise that our broader goals are unlikely to be achieved in the short term. <br>
<br>
Do you pay taxes? <br>
<br>
Yes. Citizens who reside or work outside the Imperial Capital must subscribe to the laws that apply in their country of residence or employment, in the same way that all foreign nationals residing or working in other countries do. <br>
<br>
Where does your population live? <br>
<br>
At the present day the citizens of Pacifica can be found spread all over the World. <br>
<br>
What are your politics? <br>
<br>
Because Pacifica is not a political party it does not espouse or promote a fixed political agenda. Political views are a Constitutionally guaranteed matter of personal choice, and the Empire embraces Citizens supporting a broad diversity of such views - from socialism at one end of the spectrum, to libertarianism at the other. <br>
<br>
What are your principles? <br>
<br>
Pacifica is founded on two important principles: <br>
A. That the only demonstrably viable basis for sound, stable, progressive, maximally beneficent government is the recognition that individual rights and collective social responsibilities are intrinsically co-existent; and <br>
B. That eventual global social, economic and political union is both inevitable and desirable. <br>
Apart from the above, Pacifica supports a range of extremely liberal Constitutionally guaranteed personal freedoms and responsibilities founded on a belief in the fundamental equality of all people. <br>
<br>
What are your religious views? <br>
<br>
Pacifica is a Catholic State, but the Constitution guaranties freedom of cult to all citizens. <br>
<br>
What does it cost to join? <br>
<br>
There are no fees to become a Citizen of the Empire of Pacifica. <br>
<br>
How do I become a Citizen of the Empire of Pacifica? <br>
<br>
Those wishing to apply for Citizenship in Pacifica can use the Consular Services offered in our Web Site. <br>
<br>
To become a citizen do I have to leave my Micornation? <br>
<br>
No, Pacifica is a &quot;Real Nation&quot;, therefore your participation in &quot;Virtual Micronations&quot;, Simulations or RPG does not affect your participation in Pacifica. <br>
<br>
What can I do as a Citizen of Pacifica? <br>
<br>
Almost anything! <br>
Pacifica is the First Primarily non Territorial Sovran State with Portuguese as official Language, and as such opportunities for participation are essentially unlimited. <br>
<br>
Participation in the public administration of the Empire is encouraged. Citizens may join the Imperial Senate via election or appointment, be appointed to the Judicature or function in diplomatic or protocol roles. <br>
<br>
Citizens may also explore business or trade opportunities, promote open discussions or debate policy positions, or provide practical, material or in-kind support as their level of motivation and circumstances allow. <br>
<br>
